                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#57v"/> A small cross in the margin marks the midpoint of the psalms. 
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a01">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#156r"/> to the right of the cross: Note from a student of Ge’ez
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#156r"/>, to the right of the cross: Note from a student of Ge’ez
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#156v"/> scrawls
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e04">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#10r #18v #31r #39r"/>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#55v #72r #153v"/>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#66r #80v #84v"/>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#10r #17r #58r"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e05">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#2v"/>, line 25; 16v, line 6: text has a line above and below to signal its erasure to correct homoeoteleuton
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e06">
                        <desc>
                          The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to complete the line of text above or below the end of the line
                          (throughout). But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout)
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
